On 2007-12-03 19:25:54 -0800, Bart Schaefer wrote:
> Try it this way, where the -e option is not a quoted string:
> 
> ------------------
> #!/usr/bin/env zsh
> 
> echo foo | tee \
> $({ xterm -e zsh -fic "tty >&3 ; exec sleep 99999999" 3>&1 & } | read -E)
> ------------------

Thanks, this works.

